## Intent → visual lane → `outputSchema`

Map **intent** (intake-routing) to a **card schema** the product owns. Multiple intents may share one schema if the layout fits; split intents (e.g. COMPARISON vs DECISION) may get distinct schemas when UX diverges.

| Intent lane | Visual feel | `outputSchema` (string) |
|-------------|-------------|-------------------------|
| SHOPPING | Product grid, images, price, CTA | `SHOPPING_CARD` |
| COMPARISON | Side-by-side / swipeable compare | `COMPARISON_CARD` |
| RESEARCH | Article-like, key facts, sources | `RESEARCH_CARD` |
| FIND_PLACE | Map + list, distance, rating | `PLACE_CARD` |
| FIND_PERSON | Profile card, links, no fake photo | `PERSON_CARD` |
| SCHEDULE_PREP | Meeting brief | `MEETING_BRIEF` |
| DRAFT | Clean document, copy-first | `DRAFT_CARD` |
| DECISION | Verdict up top, evidence below | `DECISION_CARD` |
| LEGAL_FINANCIAL | Clauses + plain English | `LEGAL_FINANCIAL_CARD` (or split `CLAUSE_CARD` + summary by product) |
| EXPLAIN | TL;DR, steps, analogy | `EXPLAIN_CARD` |
| SUMMARIZE | Pull quotes, key points, reading time | `SUMMARY_CARD` |
| CONTENT_IDE | Idea cards, swipe / save-discard pattern | `IDEA_CARDS` |
| TASK_UNCLEAR | Single clarify prompt (minimal chrome) | align with existing clarify / `guidance` — product decides |
| Others (LIFE_ADMIN, TRACK_MONITOR, …) | Fallback or dedicated schema as product matures | `RESEARCH_CARD` / `GUIDANCE_CARD` / intent-specific |

When adding a schema, add **Zod** (or equivalent) validation server-side and a **single** React subtree under `app/components/sections/prep-detail-sections/`.

