## Quality rules (agentic loop)

- Prefer **≥3 distinct sources** for search-heavy intents when claiming recommendations (regenerate query once on low-quality SERP — see intake-routing).
- **Shopping:** ≥3 products with **real** prices and URLs when possible; never placeholder images.
- **Places:** ≥3 candidates with ratings when the ask implies a shortlist; **map** only with real coordinates or omit.
- **People:** omit `photo` rather than wrong person.
- **Meeting brief:** include **recent** angle (e.g. news) when user asked for prep before a meeting.
- **Confidence:** surface **low** when sources are thin; never pad with fiction.
- **Latency target:** favor parallel execution; simple intents **~30s**, complex **~60s** (tune with timeouts in config — see `pem-backend.mdc`).

